Almond Cake
  --America's Test Kitchen

1 1/2 c + 1/3 c blanched sliced almonds, toasted
3/4 c (3 3/4oz) ap flour
3/4 tsp salt
1/8 tsp baking powder
4 large eggs
1 1/4 c (8 3/4oz) + 2 tbsp sugar
1 tbsp + 1/2 tsp grated lemon zest (2 lemons)
3/4 tsp almond extract
5 tbsp unsalted butter, melted
1/3 c vegetable oil

Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat to 300F. Grease 9" round cake pan and line with parchment paper. Pulst 1 1/2 c almonds, flour, salt, baking powder, and baking soda in food processor until almonds are finely ground, 5-10 pulses. Transfer almond mixture to bowl. Process eggs, 1 1/4 c sugar, 1 tbsp lemon zest, and almond extract in now empty processor until very pale yellow, ~2 min. With processor running, add melted butter and oil in steady stream, until incorporated. Add almond mixture and pulse to combine, 4-5 pulses. Transfer to prepared pan. Using your fingers, combine remaining 2 tbsp sugar and 1/2 tsp lemon zest in small bowl until fragrant, 5-10 s. Sprinkle top of cake evenly with remaining 1/3 c almonds followed by sugar-zest mixture. Bake until center of cake is set and bounces back when gently pressed and a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 55-65 min, rotating pan after 40 min. Let cake cool in pan on wire rack for 15 min. Run paring knife around sides of pan. Invert cake onto greased wire rack, discard parchmnet, and reinvert cake onto second wire rack. Let cake cool, ~2 hrs. Cut into wedges and serve. Can store at room temp for up to 3 days.


Notes: Can sub slivered almonds for blanched, sliced almonds.
